Website - Class in classes
Website class represents one website the user wants to monitorize One website is characterized by : A check Interval - it is given by the user in seconds - it tells us how often we do a check on a website A date - when the website was added in the monitoring system A unique id A String url - it must be an existing url
Website(Integer, String, Integer, Date) - Constructor for class classes.Website
First Constructor for a website This first method is useful when we retrieve a website stored in the database.
Website(String, Integer) - Constructor for class classes.Website
Second Constructor for a website This second method is useful when we need to create a Website Object from the CLUI In fact, we only know the url and idCheck in the CLUI, the idWebsite and date will be generated when the website is stored in the database.
